The Joomla! content management system lets you create webpages of various types using extensions. There are 5 basic types of extensions: components

'description':

Components are larger extensions that produce the major content for your site. Each component has one or more "views" that control how content is displayed.In the Joomla! administrator there are additional extensions such as Menus

'

Modules are small blocks of content that can be displayed in positions on a web page. The menus on this site are displayed in modules. The core of Joomla! includes 17 separate modules ranging from login to search to random images. Each module has a name that starts mod_ but when it displays it has a title. In the descriptions in this section
'published':
the titles are the same as the names.
